comments.body:
@vrothberg @Luap99 thanks for the feedback. I guess I just see a sort of gap in pod commands and was looking to fill it. Maybe there is a simpler version of what I am thinking where we can split a single container out of a pod but keep it in existence. 

I do see the similarity to `podman container clone` but I feel as though it would make sense to maybe make something like `podman pod detach $CID` and `podman pod attach $CID` in terms of attaching and detaching a container to/from a pod. I like the idea of pods having their own commands that don't utilize container commands explicitly.

@rhatdan @mheon thoughts on a surefire way to add/remove containers from a pod once already created?
